RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALL ME ANDY bumped with an inner rival soon after the start, recovered and advanced to an inside tracking position entering the turn, took aim on the clear leader two wide entering the lane, bid in upper stretch, gained an advantage entering midstretch, then inched clear in the final sixteenth before holding safely from an inner rallying rival late. TOP OF THE STREET saved ground off of the pace, offered a rail rally in the final furlong, quickly closed in on the leaders in the late stages, but ran out of ground. SONOFASHIP set the pace in the two path, but was headed by an outer bidder at the furlong grounds and lost place to an inner foe late. HAILSTORM chased in the four path and outside of rivals while within striking range around the turn, but was outmoved by an inner rival entering the lane, ran on evenly while in pursuit through midstretch and lost place an inner rival in the final sixteenth. LOU'S LEGACY bumped with an outer rival early on, laid off of the pace in the four to five path and lacked a bid. CARD TRICK broke slowly before shifting inwardly, then trailed in the two path and made little impact. HIGGINS BOAT pressed the leader from the three path, but weakened between horses entering the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMP HOPE laid off of the pace in the three to four path, fanned to the six path in upper stretch, rallied to reel in the new leader at the sixteenth pole and edged ahead. HOZIER settled far back along the inside, trailed between horses entering the far turn, took that bend at the rear in the two to three path, got floated to the nine path entering the lane, yet rallied willingly outside of foes to gain show in the final sixteenth. GENTLE SOUL trailed along the inside, saved ground around the far turn after moving out of last, then improved two wide in upper stretch, but flattened out along the rail in the final furlong. ENGLISH BEE pressed two wide, vied around the far turn as outer rivals applied pressure, led entering the lane, but was headed by an inner bidder leaving the three sixteenths pole and weakened between horses in midstretch. TRADEMARK stalked three wide, pressed into the far turn as an outer rival forced his hand, but gave way turning for home. STITCHED set the pace inside of a prompting foe, vied with that one around the far turn, but got headed entering the lane and weakened. CADDO RIVER pursued from midpack in the three to four path entering the backstretch, moved forward to press outside of the top trio entering the far turn, sustained striking range around that bend, but weakened in the five path and between horses in upper stretch.

(If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One mile.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIDDEN PATH pressed two wide, vied around the far turn, gained an advantage from an inner BLUE DEVIL entering the lane, but shifted in and bumped that one in upper stretch, exchanged a pair of more bumps with his inner counterpart while sparring in midstretch, battled gamely between horses through the final sixteenth and narrowly prevailed. BLUE DEVIL set the pace inside of a pressing rival, got headed by that one entering the lane, took a bump from him in upper stretch while sustaining a duel, battled into midstretch while exchanging contact twice once again, fought on gamely through the late stages, but just missed. UNLEASH THE POWER bumped with an inner rival before before steadying out of crowded quarters early on, saved ground off of the pace, improved inside of foes down the backstretch to track from the pocket around the far turn, tipped outside of the embattled leading pair entering the lane, sustained a grinding gain to offer a bid in the final furlong, but was kept at bay. SOLID COUNTRY GOLD saved ground far back, improved inside of foes in upper stretch, shifted four wide entering the final sixteenth and offered a good late kick but ran out of ground. MAASAI WARRIOR bumped with an outer foe while put to tight quarters before taking up early on, trailed two wide, saved ground around the far turn, rallied strongly along the rail through the lane, vacated it in the final sixteenth and belated surged between the leaders at the wire. POLICY OPTION pursued from midpack along the inside, steadied entering the backstretch, lost position between horses approaching the far turn, then was shuffled back while fading turning for home. SANTORINI stalked three wide, chased within striking range around the far turn but gave way once floated four wide in upper stretch. GAMER pursued from midpack three to four wide, fanned five wide entering the lane and yielded. HE'S A ANGEL laid off of the pace two to three wide around the first turn, then in the four path around the far turn and failed to menace. PLAUSIBLE DENILE tracked in midpack two wide and between horses, but checked nearing the backstretch, retreated to the rear in the three path entering the far turn and failed to factor. SAM STORMY tracked two wide and between horses, but steadied around the first turn before shifting three wide, and faded between horses around the far turn. A LA CARTE stalked along the inside, but was surpassed by an inner rival at the half mile pole and weakened between horses around the far turn. THE RIDER AND TRAINER OF BLUE DEVIL CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF HIDDEN PATH FOR INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH, BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS.
